text: The Kokowalandja were an indigenous Australian people of northern Queensland. ==Country== The Kokowalandja are stated, by Norman Tindale, to have had a territorial extent of some , around the headwaters of the east Normanby River, with a westward extension to the Great Dividing Range. ==Alternative names== * Koko Katji. (Kokojelandji exonym). ==Notes== ==Citations== ==Sources== * Category:Aboriginal peoples of Queensland
title: Kokowalandja
